<br>
1) The same item marked with the cheapest price will get sold first, doesn't mean the other ones with higher prices won't get sold at all.<br>
<br>
2) Those who sell it cheap probably have different motivation than you.  You might be in it for the profit.  They might be unloading a bunch after skill up sessions or just trying to get them sold and be done with.  If something is not profitable to you, its probably not profitable to them.  That's means they have no reason to do it perpetually just to screw you.  So just wait it out.<br>
<br>
3) There is an unlimited supply of components so there are potentially unlimited supply of whatever you are making.  Don't bet your livelihood in one thing.  Everything gets cheaper over time (except 1. after Verant add focus effects on them, and 2.  some off-server maniacs start to play around to jack up the prices 2x or 3x, then the rest of the residient merchants stupidly join in and buy off of each others unknowingly and can't bring the prices back down because they'll lose a big chunk of change, a la Fungi Tunic).<br>
<br>
4) If you want to fix prices (if you care, that's illegal in RL), just buy up all the cheap ones and sell them at your price.<br>
<br>
Not sure if you are around for the GVD duel between Aalandan and Zarianna (/wave /hug to both).  Same thing.  GVD was going for 20K.  Zari was doing skill ups and start selling them for 5k to fund her tradeskills.  Aalandan jumped up and down wildly and whine and complain on every boards that care.  So what happened?  Aalandan drop his to 5k, got a lot of customers.  Guess what?  Prices of GVD are back up.  Zari is done with tinkering so supply of GVD went back down.  What's the cost of the components?  400pp not counting the farmed ones.  <br>
<br>
Its pure economics.  Its not about your cost or what it cost you to skill up to 250.  Its not about how much its worth to the buyer or how much it should be worth based on how it compares to other items.  It is all about supply and demand.  <br>
